<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-11-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-11-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="581" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d581">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Porter</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Embassy
                                        of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-11-06"><hi rend="italic">November 6,
                                1900</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 748.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor of acknowledging receipt
                            of your No. 839, of October 23, directing me, at the instance of the
                            Secretary of the Navy, to convey to the French Government the thanks of
                            the Navy Department for the facilities given by the authorities of Havre
                            on the occasion of the death of a landsman belonging to the U. S. S. <hi rend="italic">Hartford</hi>, and for the courtesies extended on that
                            occasion.</p>
                        <p>Your instructions were complied with under date of the 5th instant.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Horace Porter.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>